 To find the perfect square factors of 180, we multiply the prime factors of 180 together
\begin{align*}
180 &= 1 \cdot 2 \\
180 + 180 &= 182 \\
\end{align*}
So far we have a total of 182 perfect squares.
To find the number of perfect squares that are factors of 180 of each prime factor, multiply the primes together.
\begin{align*}
180 &= 1 \cdot 2 \cdot 3 \\
175 &= 1 \cdot 2 \cdot 5 \\
\end{align*}
Next, we multiply the primes together as well as the 5s.
\begin{align*}
180 &= 1 \cdot 2 \cdot 3 \cdot 2 \\
173 &= 3 \\
\end{align*}
Finally, the 9:
\begin{align*}
180 &= 1 \cdot 2 \cdot 3 \cdot 3 \\
175 &= 3 \cdot 5 \\
\end{align*}
So, there are 2 rather than 3 perfect square factors. The answer is: $2$

